SIMPLE: nameless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nameless
<hw>Name"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Without a name; not
having been given a name; <as>as, a <ex>nameless</ex> star</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Waller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Undistinguished; not noted or famous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>nameless</qex> dwelling and an unknown name.</q>
<rj><qau>Harte.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not known or mentioned by name; anonymous; <as>as, a
<ex>nameless</ex> writer</as>.</def>⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Nameless</xex>
pens.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Atterbury.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Unnameable; indescribable; inexpressible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But what it is, that is not yet known; what⟦br⟧
I can not name; 't is <qex>nameless</qex> woe,I wot.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a <qex>nameless</qex> horror of the man.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Namelessly</ent>⟦br⟧
